---
/* ============================================================================
   Cloudflare Web Analytics
   ============================================================================
   Privacy-friendly, cookie-free traffic measurement. Free at our volume.
   The beacon script reports page views and Web Vitals to Cloudflare's
   analytics endpoint; no cookie banner needed because nothing is stored
   on the visitor's device.

   Setup:
     1. dash.cloudflare.com > Analytics & Logs > Web Analytics > Add a site
     2. Cloudflare gives you a token (a hex string).
     3. Set PUBLIC_CF_ANALYTICS_TOKEN in .env locally and in
        Cloudflare Pages > Settings > Build > Variables and secrets.
     4. Push a small commit (or click Retry deployment) so the new build
        bakes the token into the beacon script.

   This component renders nothing if the token is missing, so local dev
   and any preview deploy without the variable stays clean.
   ============================================================================ */

// PUBLIC_ prefix is required because the script tag runs in the browser.
// The value is inlined at build time (this is a prerendered layout), so
// the env var must be set on the BUILD environment in Cloudflare, not
// the runtime environment.
const token = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_CF_ANALYTICS_TOKEN ?? '';
const hasToken = token.length > 0;

// JSON-encode the token into the data attribute exactly the way
// Cloudflare's snippet does. JSON.stringify takes care of escaping in
// case the token ever contains characters that would break the markup.
const beaconConfig = JSON.stringify({ token });
---

{hasToken && (
  <script
    defer
    src="https://static.cloudflareinsights.com/beacon.min.js"
    data-cf-beacon={beaconConfig}
  ></script>
)}
